Pattern of pedal glands (
Figure 6
). UpG subconical and slightly shorter than MeG in anterior chaetigers, becoming oblong and as wide as MeG in middle chaetigers. LoG elliptical and subequal to UpG in anterior chaetigers, dissapearing towards middle chaetigers. MeG elliptical and twice larger than PoG in anterior chaetigers, becoming rounded in middle chaetigers. PoG becoming shorter than middle chaetigers.
